text = "The compliment of a number to a given value v of 10^n is equal to 10^n – v. This value is used in addition and subtraction to carry over or borrow digits. To read the compliment number on this abacus, you must read the beads that are not counted, ignoring trailing zeros, and add 1 to the rod closest to the right with a value greater than 0."

